\section{Introduction}\label{intro}
The study of slant submanifold in an almost Hermitian manifold was initiated by Chen \cite{BYC} and it attained momentum  when Papaghuic \cite{Pap} presented semi-slant submanifolds for the generalization of slant submanifolds and CR-submanifolds. Later, Etayo \cite{Etayo} initiated the study of quasi-slant submanifolds as an another generalization of slant submanifold which is further carried out by Chen-Garay with name pointwise slant submanifold \cite{CG}. 
On the other hand, Bishop-Niell started the concept of warped product (or, more generally warped bundle) which is one of the
most effective generalization of pseudo-Riemannian products \cite{RB}. The speculation of warped product has recognized various significant contributions in pseudo-Riemannian geometry, and has been successfully employed in different models of space-time, Ricci flow, Hamiltonian spaces, general relativity and black holes (c.f., \cite{Attarchi, Carrot, Kreitler, Hung}). Furthermore, the theory of warped product and slant submanifolds was studied by several geometers in different known spaces (see \cite{ Atceken, Chen2, Chnwp1, Carri}). Recently, Sahin \cite{Sahin} and Park \cite{Park, Park2} studied the warped product pointwise slant and semi-slant submanifolds in Kaehler and contact manifolds respectively.

In the present work, we study the geometry of pointwise pseudo-slant warped product submanifold of a para-Kaehler manifold. The summary of the article is as follows. In Sect. \ref{pre}, the basic informations about para-Kaehler manifold, submanifold and pointwise slant submanifold are given. Sect. \ref{ppss} deals with the construction of pointwise pseudo-slant submaniold, the condition of integrablity and totally geodesic foliation for the distributions allied to the characterization of a pointwise pseudo-slant submanifold. In Sect. \ref{wppss}, we first prove some preparatory results and then obtain a necessary and sufficient condition for a submanifold to be locally warped product. Finally, we give an example illustrating pointwise pseudo-slant warped product submanifold of a para-Kaehler manifold.   

