\section{Pointwise pseudo-slant submanifolds}\label{ppss}
In this section, we define and study pointwise pseudo-slant submanifold of a para-Kaehler manifold $\widetilde{M}^{2n}$. 
\begin{dfn}
Let $M$ be an isometrically immersed submanifold in a para-Kaehler manifold $\widetilde{M}^{2n}$. Then we say that $M$ is a {\it pointwise pseudo-slant submanifold} if it is furnished with the pair of orthogonal distribution $(\mathfrak{D}^{\bot},\mathfrak{D}_{\theta})$ satisfying the conditions:
\begin{itemize}
\item[(i)] $TM = \mathfrak{D}^{\bot}\oplus \mathfrak{D}_{\theta}$,
\item[(ii)] the distribution $\mathfrak{D}{^\bot}$ is totally real distribution under $J$, i.e., $J(\mathfrak{D}{^\bot})\subseteq \Gamma(TM){^\bot}$ and
\item[(iii)] the distribution $\mathfrak{D}_{\theta}$ is pointwise slant distribution with slant function $\theta$. 
\end{itemize}
\end{dfn}
