    \item [(b)] pseudo-slant submanifold when its slant function $\theta$ is globally constant, in particular if $d_1 \neq 0$ and $\theta = 0$  then $M$ is a $\mathcal{P}\mathcal{R}$-submanifold \cite{Chen} and if $\theta = \pi/2$ then $M$ is a totally real submanifold \cite{Chen3}.
